<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-10-21T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-10-21T07:00:00-05:00" n="243" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890g.01/227: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in Great Britain</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi></persName>)
                                <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-21T12:00:00+00:00">October 21,
                                1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received October 21—10:10
                            a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>302. Department’s 277, October 19, 2 p.m. Inquiry was made last week of
                            the Foreign Office which stated the draft of Jafar Pasha’s communication
                            had been referred to Baghdad and an answer was expected momentarily. I
                            am further assured this morning that Colonial Office will appropriately
                            press this matter.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>